SIMPLE: chitter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chitter
<hw>Chit"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Chatter</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To chirp in a tremulous
manner, as a bird.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To shiver or chatter with cold.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chitterling</ent>⟦br⟧
